RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY GREGORY tracked leader while bit off the rail into the backstretch, moved up and challenged past quarter marker, gained front and kicked clear in the lane. SPUN BEAUTIFUL reserved early, chased three then four wide into and around first turn, continued three deep and outside, roused on last bend, rallied bit outside and was along for the place. COWLITZ sped to the front, set pace from along the rail, was overtaken on the second turn and weakened from the inside. MY LITE NITE chased two or three wide into and around the first turn, between rivals early on the backstretch, angled in leaving last bend and failed to threaten. ARCTIC FIRE hopped slightly at the start to be off behind the field, trailed from the inside, dropped back around the last bend and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Cowlitz
ENTRY.COMMENT: early foot, pace, rail, overtaken 2nd turn, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Arctic Fire
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped break, chased, inside, dropped back, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Gregory
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 2wide, past 1/4, led, cleared lane

ENTRY.NAME: My Lite Nite
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3wide, betwen, angled in upper, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Spun Beautiful
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 3-4wide, roused 2nd turn, gained 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 57. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STEEL NERVES outsprinted inside rival to the first turn, kicked clear early on the backstretch, stretched that cushion to the final bend and safely held while shown the stick in the lane. OUR GIRL ASHLEY broke out slightly, came off the rail into and around the first turn, remained in two path and clearly held the place. ENGEE OMBEE forced in at the start and put in tight quarters chased off the rail then three wide to last turn, remained wide and colared foe late for third. JERSEY BIRD settled outside, chased three wide and outside OUR GIRL ASHLEY, continued well off the rail, weakened bit in final sixteenth and lost the show. LUTE'S DIAMOND was forced in at the start, chased inside then on the two path and failed to menace. HAMPTONRUN broke in some, forced the early pace inside winner, lost contact with leader early on the backstretch, remained along the rail and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Our Girl Ashley
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, 2wide 1st,between, inside, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Lute's Diamond
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in break, chased, inside, 2wide, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Engee Ombee
ENTRY.OWNER: Sandlot Racing Stables and Lininger Paul
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in break, tight, 3wide to 2nd turn, gained show

ENTRY.NAME: Hamptonrun
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, forced pace, rail, lost contact, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Steel Nerves
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2path, cleared 3/8, stretched lead, safely held,driving

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Bird
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, outside, 3wide, outside foe, weakened, lost 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MO SUGAFOOT taken in hand shortly after the break, bit rank early from the outside, three wide into the backstretch, moved up some then boldly moved past leader on two path, kicked away and held despite having lead dissolve late. VISION OF THE KAT between rivals and inside winner early, stalked on two path, could not go with MO SUGARFOOT around last turn, tipped out into the lane and found her best stride late. LILY PAD LAKE gained lead from along the rail into first turn, padded that cushion early on the backstretch, relinquished command on the last bend and weakened inside.

ENTRY.NAME: Lily Pad Lake
ENTRY.COMMENT: early lead, inside, padded margin, overtaken 2nd turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Vision of the Kat
ENTRY.COMMENT: between, 2wide, stalked, inside winner, 3wd, best stride late

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Sugafoot
ENTRY.COMMENT: taken in hand,3wide, 2wide move, led 2nd turn, cleared, held

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SNICKER'N DAN dueled from the inside to the initial turn, gained advantage then edged away on the backstretch, retained clear cushion to the lane and was kept to task late to prove best. BOY HOWDY contested the early issue while outside winner, dropped back slightly leaving the first turn, remained prominent to last turn, failed to threaten winner but safely retained second. SMOKE AND BURN was antsy in the gate then broke slow, dropped well back the opening quarter, shifted out around the final bend, came four wide into the stretch, rallied and gained minor award. PIVOTAL FEVER hopped slightly leaving the gate, angled over early, chased outside rival, was two then three wide to the stretch, roused but never responsed. CAPES HOT ROCKET chased along the fence early, came off the rail leaving first turn, angled back to the rail and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Capes Hot Rocket
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased, rail, came out bit, back to rail into lane, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Smoke and Burn
ENTRY.COMMENT: antsy gate, broke slow, dropped back, angled out, gained show

ENTRY.NAME: Snicker'n Dan
ENTRY.OWNER: Beckner Teri L and Gallus Bjorn M
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside duel, gained lead, edged away, kept to task late

ENTRY.NAME: Pivotal Fever
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped slightly start, angled in, 2wide, 3wide, lacked response

ENTRY.NAME: Boy Howdy
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled, 2wide, forced pace, stalked, 2wide, held place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 82. Starter Allowance Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PULPITS POWER settled off the leaders, moved up from the inside to the second turn, found clear path from between rivals in upper stretch, grabbed lead a sixteenth out and powered away. SPEEDY TOM contested the early pace from the inside, emerged with lead on the first turn, set pace along the rail to the second turn, resisted briefly when challenged, then was overtaken and held for the place. DEBT MONGER broke out bit, angled over into first turn, continued bit off the rail, dropped back bit early on the last turn, swung out five then six wide into the stretch and rallied belatedly from the far outside. SKEESIX among the speed brigade while two wide and between rivals to the first turn, dropped off the pace, later drifted three then four wide on the second turn and lacked needed rally. TIZ INDY hopped at the start to be off behind the field, three deep and between leaders into first turn, tracked leader to last bend, drifted four then five wide into the stretch and weakened. DUMB LUCK bumped with inside rival early, caught four abreast into first turn, continued on outside on backstretch, drifted out further on the last bend, then angled in some and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Speedy Tom
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, duel, led, pace, collared drive, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Pulpits Power
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, found clear path, rallied, led 1/16, cleared

ENTRY.NAME: Skeesix
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2wd, btwn, stalked, drifted 4wide 2nd turn, lacked rally

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Indy
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, bumped early, 3deep, btwn, 4-5wd into lane

ENTRY.NAME: Dumb Luck
ENTRY.COMMENT: bpd early, 4deep, dropped back, wide, angled in, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Debt Monger
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, angled over, swung 5-6 wide 2nd turn, into lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FERNDALE RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 7000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRAW SOME pressured the pacesetter around first two turns, moved alongside that foe and gained brief lead early on the last bend, lost that advantage, then battled back, inched away and held off that rival late. FOYT broke out and bumped rival, was bit rank into first turn, lugged out on that bend, came back over, stalked pace, shifted back out three wide, bid then gained slim advantage, then could not match winner in the drive. FRESNO CHILE settled four wide, angled over bit, chased two then three wide around second bend, came in some in late stages and held third. NOTCH unhurried early, raced three wide, later shifted in some and failed to threaten. COLTON'S TIGER bumped with inside rival at the start, gained lead and set pace from the inside, lost command passing quarter marker and weakened. HOLY SMOKES was fanned four wide around the first turn, angled back over, saved ground thereafter and also weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Foyt
ENTRY.COMMENT: bpd brk, bit rank, lugged out 1st, brief lead, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Colton's Tiger
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break, pace, inside, lost lead 1/4, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Holy Smokes
ENTRY.OWNER: Swanson Steve E and Swanson Christine E
ENTRY.COMMENT: fanned 4wide 1st turn, angled over, found rail, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Notch
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, 3wide, shifted over, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Fresno Chile
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide, angled over, 2-3 wore down rivals, 2nd turn, held show

ENTRY.NAME: Draw Some
ENTRY.OWNER: Eaton Terri Gibson Joe H and Reagan Dee
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced pace, 2wide, bid, led, battled back, held off foe
